chatgpt_double_star.new_statement: Abortion laws should be guided by protecting health and dignity while treating the moral stakes of fetal development with seriousness, without assuming one view of personhood will persuade everyone. A broadly workable approach is to ensure prompt, nonpunitive care in cases of medical risk, rape, or severe fetal anomaly; set any remaining limits in ways clinicians can apply; and avoid policies that drive care underground. At the same time, society should reduce the pressures that lead to unwanted pregnancies by expanding contraception, comprehensive sex education, prenatal and postpartum healthcare, and practical supports for parenting and adoption.
